item.title: 国际能源署认为经济逆风阻碍了需求增长
item.description: 国际能源机构（International Energy Agency）周四表示，疫后动荡的平息和经济前景的阴霾将抑制今年的需求增长，尽管航运中断会带来短期提振。【原文：The settling down of post-pandemic turbulence and a cloudy economic outlook will rein in demand growth this year, the International Energy Agency said on Thursday, even as shipping disruptions provide a short-term boost.】

item.title: 经合组织称瑞银拯救瑞士信贷为瑞士带来新风险
item.description: 经济合作与发展组织（Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development）周四表示，瑞银一年前对瑞士信贷（Credit Suisse）的拯救性收购给瑞士经济带来了 "新的风险和挑战"，这是对该交易表示担忧的最新一个国际论坛。【原文：UBS's rescue takeover of Credit Suisse a year ago has created "new risks and challenges" for the Swiss economy, the Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development said on Thursday, the latest international forum to raise concerns about the deal.】

item.title: KKR 向恩凯维发出 30 亿美元公开收购要约
item.description: 私募股权公司 KKR 周四表示，已向德国电力和能源生产商 Encavis 发出 28 亿欧元（30.6 亿美元）的收购要约。【原文：Private equity firm KKR has launched a 2.8 billion-euro ($3.06 billion) takeover offer for German electricity and energy producer Encavis , the company said on Thursday.】

item.title: 德意志银行首席执行官 2023 年薪酬降至 870 万欧元
item.description: 德意志银行（Deutsche Bank）首席执行官克里斯蒂安-斯温（Christian Sewing）周四在其年度报告中表示，在利润下降之后，该行2023年的收入为870万欧元（约合952万美元），略低于2022年的890万欧元。【原文：Deutsche Bank CEO Christian Sewing earned 8.7 million euros ($9.52 million) in 2023, down slightly from 8.9 million euros in 2022 after a fall in profit, the bank said in its annual report on Thursday.】

item.title: 日元疲软，新加坡盈科将重启日本豪华滑雪胜地基金
item.description: 日本北部一个价值 14.2 亿美元的豪华滑雪场项目背后的新加坡投资者 Patience Capital Group 正在洽谈重新开放其基金，以吸引急于在日本央行收紧货币政策之前进入的新投资者。【原文：Patience Capital Group, the Singapore-based investor behind a $1.42 billion luxury ski project in northern Japan, is in talks to reopen its fund to new investors eager to get in before tightening by the Bank of Japan.】

item.title: 金融服务管理局称啤酒商百威英博股票被暂停交易
item.description: 比利时金融服务和市场管理局（FSMA）周四表示，安海斯-布希英博公司股票暂停交易，等待发布新闻稿，但未作详细说明。【原文：Anheuser-Busch InBev's shares were suspended from trading on Thursday pending the publication of a press release, Belgium's Financial Services and Markets Authority (FSMA) said without elaborating.】

item.title: 中国外交部称美国提议的 TikTok 禁令 "不公平
item.description: 中国外交部发言人周四表示，以国家安全为由削弱其他国家的竞争优势 "毫无公平可言"，并批评了美国提出的强制剥离或禁止 TikTok 的法案。【原文：There is "no fairness to speak of" in citing national security to reduce the competitive advantage of other countries, a spokesperson of the Chinese foreign ministry said on Thursday, criticising a U.S. bill to force a TikTok divestiture or ban.】

item.title: 欧洲股市徘徊在历史最高水平附近；美国经济数据即将出炉
item.description: 欧洲股市周四开盘走高，一系列乐观的企业最新消息为其提供了支撑，而在美国关键经济数据公布前，投资者仍持谨慎态度。【原文：European shares opened higher on Thursday, supported by a raft of optimistic corporate updates, while investors remained cautious ahead of key economic data from the United States.】

item.title: 国防开支推动销售增长，莱茵金属欢呼 "新十年
item.description: 德国军火制造商莱茵金属公司（Rheinmetall）周四表示，随着乌克兰战争推动北约集团国防开支的增加，该公司预计今年的销售额将创下历史新高，盈利能力也将有所提高，这一趋势将在未来几年内推动该公司的发展。【原文：German arms manufacturer Rheinmetall said on Thursday it expects record sales and increased profitability this year, as the war in Ukraine drives up defence spending in the NATO bloc, in a trend set to buoy the company for years to come.】

item.title: 消息人士称，中国腾讯接管了字节跳动的两个视频游戏团队
item.description: 据一位熟悉内情的人士透露，在字节跳动去年退出游戏业务后，中国腾讯已接管了字节跳动的两个视频游戏部门。【原文：China's Tencent has taken over two ByteDance video games units after ByteDance retreated from the gaming business last year, according to a person familiar with the matter.】

item.title: 瑞士下议院支持从获救银行收回薪酬的计划
item.description: 瑞士议会下院周三晚些时候明确通过一项动议，要求一家大型银行的高级管理层在该银行必须用公共资金拯救的情况下，归还其过去十年收入的一半。【原文：Switzerland's lower house of parliament late on Wednesday clearly passed a motion to make senior management of a major bank return half their income over the previous decade if the lender has to be rescued with public money.】

item.title: 独家报道全球供应过剩，中国买家取消或推迟购买澳大利亚小麦
item.description: 直接了解这些交易的贸易消息人士称，中国小麦进口商已经取消或推迟了约 100 万公吨澳大利亚小麦的进口，原因是全球小麦库存不断增加，拖累了小麦价格。【原文：Chinese wheat importers have cancelled or postponed about one million metric tons of Australian wheat imports, trade sources with direct knowledge of the deals said, as growing world stockpiles drag down prices.】

item.title: 阿斯利康将斥资 10.5 亿美元收购 Amolyt Pharma，以扩大罕见病产品组合
item.description: 制药商阿斯利康（AstraZeneca）周四表示，将以10.5亿美元现金收购专注于罕见内分泌疾病的Amolyt Pharma公司，以增强其罕见病产品组合。【原文：Drugmaker AstraZeneca said on Thursday it will acquire rare endocrine diseases-focused firm Amolyt Pharma for $1.05 billion in cash, in a bid to boost its rare diseases portfolio.】

item.title: Deliveroo 盈利超预期，2024 年将实现正现金流
item.description: 英国送餐公司Deliveroo报告称，2023年的核心盈利将达到8500万英镑（约合1.09亿美元），好于预期。【原文：British meal delivery company Deliveroo reported better-than-expected core earnings of 85 million pounds ($109 million)for 2023, and said it expected further progress the year, when it expects to move into positive cash flow.】

item.title: 新加坡大华银行的目标是到 2026 年将私人财富资产翻一番
item.description: 新加坡大华银行（UOB）的一位高层管理人员表示，该行计划在未来几年内将其管理的私人财富资产翻一番，因为该行看好流入新加坡和东南亚的财富的增长。【原文：Singaporean lender United Overseas Bank (UOB) is planning to double its private wealth assets under management over the next couple of years as it bets on increased wealth inflows into the city-state and Southeast Asia, a top executive said.】

item.title: 甲骨文为财务和供应链软件增加人工智能生成功能
item.description: 甲骨文公司周四表示，该公司正在其企业软件阵容中增加人工智能生成功能，从而加剧了与微软和其他技术公司在向企业客户销售人工智能技术方面的竞争。【原文：Oracle on Thursday said it is adding generative artificial intelligence features across its corporate software lineup, intensifying competition with Microsoft and other technology firms to sell the technology to businesses customers.】

item.title: 路透社调查显示：巴基斯坦央行周一将维持利率不变，2024 年第二季度降息
item.description: 由于通胀风险继续存在，巴基斯坦央行周一将在连续第六次政策会议上把关键利率维持在创纪录的 22% 的水平，但大多数分析师预计今年第二季度开始降息。【原文：Pakistan's central bank is widely expected to hold its key interest rate at a record 22% for the sixth straight policy meeting on Monday as inflation risks continue to loom, but a majority of analysts expect rate cuts from the second quarter of this year.】

item.title: 西班牙 Ferrovial 公司将以 8.1 亿美元收购 IRB 基础设施信托公司 24% 的股份
item.description: 西班牙建筑巨头 Ferrovial 周四表示，将以 7.4 亿欧元（约合 8.1 亿美元）的价格收购 IRB 基础设施信托公司 24% 的股份。【原文：Spanish construction giant Ferrovial said on Thursday it will buy a 24% stake in IRB Infrastructure Trust, an investment vehicle that holds a portfolio of 12 toll road concessions in India, for 740 million euros (about $810 million).】

item.title: 在美联储宽松政策的不确定性下，中国央行周五将维持关键利率不变
item.description: 路透社的一项调查显示，在美联储降息预期时间不确定的情况下，中国央行周五展期到期的中期贷款时，预计将维持关键政策利率不变。【原文：China's central bank is expected to leave a key policy rate unchanged when it rolls over maturing medium-term loans on Friday, a Reuters survey showed, amid uncertainty over the timing of expected Federal Reserve interest rate cuts.】

item.title: 苹果供应商富士康第四季度利润同比增长 33%，超出预期
item.description: 苹果供应商富士康周四公布，受年底假日旺季销售强劲的推动，第四季度利润增长 33%。【原文：Apple supplier Foxconn reported on Thursday a 33% rise in fourth-quarter profit, boosted by strong year-end sales during the peak holiday season.】

item.title: 违约风险上升，欧洲私人信贷与银行的联系加深
item.description: 欧洲的私人信贷基金越来越多地向银行借款以提高业绩，这加剧了人们对这种相互关联所带来的更大风险的担忧。【原文：Europe's private credit funds are increasingly borrowing from banks to boost their performance, fuelling concerns about the wider risks posed by this interconnectedness.】

item.title: 据英国《金融时报》报道，Entain 正在研究出售海外博彩品牌的可能性
item.description: 据英国《金融时报》周四报道，英国博彩公司 Entain 已聘请顾问监督其几个海外品牌的可能出售。【原文：British gambling firm Entain has hired advisers to oversee the possible sale of several of its overseas brands, the Financial Times reported on Thursday.】

item.title: 中国电动汽车制造商尼欧迄今已完成 4000 万次电池更换
item.description: 中国电动汽车制造商尼欧莱博首席执行官威廉-李（William Li）周四表示，迄今为止，尼欧莱博已完成了4000万次电池更换，用充满电的电池组替换耗尽的电池，而不是将车辆插入充电点。【原文：Chinese electric vehicle maker Nio has completed 40 million battery swaps so far, CEO William Li said on Thursday, replacing depleted batteries with fully charged packs, rather than plugging the vehicle into a charging point.】

item.title: 日本货币市场为负利率的结束做好准备
item.description: 押注日本货币政策将发生历史性转变的投机者预计，潜在的新存款规则将颠覆货币市场，因此纷纷押注短期债券。【原文：Speculators betting on a historic monetary policy shift in Japan expect money markets will be upended by potential new deposit rules and are crowding into bets against short-dated bonds.】

item.title: 欧洲 投资者关注下一轮美国数据
item.description: Rae Wee 对欧洲和全球市场未来一天的展望【原文：A look at the day ahead in European and global markets from Rae Wee】

item.title: 尽管缺乏替代品，航空公司仍试图利用波音公司的困境
item.description: 波音公司的安全危机扰乱了航空公司的商业计划，航空公司高管对波音公司感到沮丧。但在由两家公司提供大型飞机的紧张市场中，他们别无选择，只能与美国飞机制造商做生意。【原文：Airline executives are frustrated with Boeing as its safety crisis has upended their business plans. But in a tight market for large aircraft supplied by two companies, they have little choice but do business with the U.S. planemaker.】

item.title: 工会称日本服务业企业提供 2013 年以来最大加薪幅度
item.description: 日本最大的产业工会 UA Zensen 周四表示，231 家企业的平均加薪幅度达到了 2013 年以来的最大值。【原文：Japan's largest industrial union UA Zensen said on Thursday that an average pay rise offered by 231 firms reached the biggest on record since 2013.】

item.title: 研究显示：各国正逐步采用数字货币，但美国落在后面
item.description: 周四进行的一项密切关注的研究显示，目前共有 134 个国家（占全球经济总量的 98%）正在探索其货币的数字版本，其中一半以上处于高级开发、试点或启动阶段。【原文：A total of 134 countries representing 98% of the global economy are now exploring digital versions of their currencies, with over half in advanced development, pilot or launch stages, a closely-followed study on Thursday showed.】

item.title: 越南总理在银行贷款疲软之际会见当地顶级企业
item.description: 越南政府表示，越南总理范明正周四会见了该国的顶级企业，讨论在银行贷款疲软的情况下支持经济活动的措施。【原文：Vietnamese Prime Minister Pham Minh Chinh on Thursday met with the country's top businesses to discuss measures to shore up economic activity amid weak bank lending, the government said.】

item.title: 达美航空公司将从 6 月 7 日起恢复飞往以色列的航班
item.description: 达美航空公司（Delta Air Lines）周三晚些时候表示，将从6月7日起恢复飞往以色列的航班，成为继10月7日哈马斯武装分子袭击以色列南部之后第二家恢复飞往以色列航班的美国主要航空公司。【原文：Delta Air Lines said late on Wednesday it will resume flights to Israel starting June 7, becoming the second major U.S. carrier to do so following the Oct. 7 attack by Hamas militants on southern Israel.】
